# Surface Kill Sheet — Flutter

A single-file Flutter implementation of the **IWCF Surface BOP Vertical Well Kill Sheet**
(API Field Units). Combines a fully interactive mobile entry form with a pixel-accurate
two-page A4 PDF export — all in one self-contained Dart file.

---

## Overview

This screen lets a well-control engineer fill in every field of the standard IWCF
Surface BOP kill sheet directly on a mobile device. Every calculated value updates
**live as you type** — no submit button, no page reload. When ready, the sheet can be
exported as a properly formatted PDF (matching the paper IWCF layout) and shared,
printed, or saved instantly.

---

## What it does

- Full **kill-sheet entry form** across 7 collapsible sections
- **Live recalculation** on every keystroke — KMW, MAASP, ICP, FCP, K/100, volumes,
  strokes, times all update instantly
- **IWCF-layout A4 PDF export** (2 pages) — download, print, or share via OS share sheet
- **5 named save slots** — save your sheet to a slot, name it, reload it later; all stored
  as JSON on-device (no cloud, no account)
- **Inline date picker** — calendar overlay anchored to the date field
- **Live well diagram** — CustomPainter schematic that redraws as casing/hole TVD values change
- **Step-down chart** — auto-generated pressure vs. strokes graph from ICP → FCP

