## Sections

| # | Section | What you enter | What it calculates |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Formation Strength Data | FST (psi), Mud Weight at Test (ppg) | Max Allowable MW (C) — rounded down to 1 dp; Initial MAASP — rounded down to whole psi |
| 2 | Current Well Data | Mud density, casing size/MD/TVD, hole size/MD/TVD | Live well schematic with depth labels |
| 3 | Pump Data | Pump displacement (bbl/stk), SPM, dynamic pressure loss (psi) | Dynamic Pressure Loss (DPL) used in ICP/FCP |
| 4 | Volumetric Data & Pump Strokes | Lengths and capacities for DP, HWDP, DC, open hole annulus, casing annulus, active surface | Volume (bbl), pump strokes (ceiling), time in minutes (ceiling) for every segment and total |
| 5 | Kick Data & Kill Mud Weight | SIDPP (psi), SICP (psi), Pit Gain (bbl) | Kill Mud Weight — rounded up to 1 dp |
| 6 | Circulating Pressures | (auto — uses values above) | ICP, FCP, K/100 strokes |
| 7 | Step-Down Chart | (auto — uses ICP, FCP, DS strokes) | Pressure step-down table (every 100 strokes) and live line graph |

