## Well Diagram

The live diagram (`_WellDiagramPainter`) is a `CustomPainter` that draws:

- White background with surface line
- Casing (grey outline, light fill) from surface to shoe
- Open hole walls below shoe to TD
- Drill pipe (dark fill) inside casing; drill collars (wider) in open hole; bit at TD
- BOP housing above surface with pressure gauges
- Three colour-coded depth lines on the left with value labels:

| Colour | Represents |
|---|---|
| 🟠 Orange | Casing Shoe TVD — surface to shoe |
| 🔵 Blue | Full Hole TVD — surface to TD |
| 🟢 Green | Open Hole depth — shoe to TD |

The diagram repaints whenever casing TVD or hole TVD changes.

---

## Step-Down Chart

`_StepDownChartPainter` builds a pressure-vs-strokes line graph automatically once
ICP, FCP, and DS total strokes are all available:

- X-axis: 0 → DS total strokes, in 100-stroke steps
- Y-axis: FCP → ICP (pressure in psi)
- Orange line connecting calculated points; green dots at each step
- Grid lines, axis labels, and axis titles drawn via `TextPainter`
- A summary bar above the table shows DS Strokes, ICP, and FCP as mini-tags

